Herakles perished in a poisoned robe, given him by his jealous wife, Deianira. When he saw that death was near at hand, he inounted his own funeral pyre, whence his spirit passed away in a cloud.

The age in which the heroes lived is known as the Heroic Age. The Greeks thought that it immediately preceded their own time, and considered a good part of the myths connected with it as true history. To this period belong also the Cen- murs‚ mythical beings, half man, half horse, celebrated for their conllicts with the Lapithae, a Thessalian people, and Herakles.
